872175272.text: "-PEDF can promote gamma-secretase-dependent proteolysis of the transmembrane portion of VEGFR1 and VEGFR2 and also inhibit VEGF induced VEGFR1 phosphorylation, or promote the dephosphorylation of this receptor, by inducing the upregulation of presenilin-1 and the subsequent aggregation of vascular endothelial protein-tyrosine phosphatase and VEGFR1."
